cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.Medical Imaging, cs.NE 

This paper deals with uncertainty estimation in medical image segmentation using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning and Bayesian neural networks, which are common in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The topic of medical imaging is also relevant to the sub-category cs.Medical Imaging. Finally, the paper proposes a method to learn the uncertainty among observers, which is related to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
